<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-06-25T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-06-25T16:00:00-05:00" n="509" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d509">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.825/48: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-06-25T17:00:00-04:00">June 25, 1934—5
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>185. Your 258, June 21, 11 a.m. and 260, June 21, 4 p.m. in regard to
                            pilotage. The Legation’s action, taken in conjunction with the
                            interested heads of Legation (other than the German Minister), in
                            acquiescing in the precautionary plan suggested by the Shanghai Consular
                            Body has the Department’s approval.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>